						               													<description>Italian board game of the '70, based on the TV show &amp;quot;Chi?&amp;quot;.&amp;#10;Each game consists of 4 rounds: memory test, ability, identikit and crime fiction.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;In the first round (memory test), the player who plays the host role (or presenter) shows an image, to each player, for a very short time (10 seconds). Each player, then, must answer to the questions and remember the details.&amp;#10;In the second round, ability, the players, to gain the priority to answer, must to insert quick as possible a colored ball into a &amp;quot;tower&amp;quot; selector.&amp;#10;The &amp;quot;Identikit&amp;quot; is a character hunt.&amp;#10;Last round is the crime fiction. Who is playing the host role selects 3 cards, one for each deck: &amp;quot;chi&amp;quot; (who), &amp;quot;dove&amp;quot; (where) and &amp;quot;che cosa&amp;quot; (what). The players must to use clues to find the solution.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;At the end, the player who scores more points is the winner.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
